{
  "text": "Rats were anesthetized using intraperitoneal injection of ketamine and xylazine (80 and 10 mg/kg, respectively; both from Sigma-Aldrich). To expose rat spinal cord, the dorsal laminectomy was performed at the T12-L1 level [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The contusion model of traumatic spinal cord was induced by dropping a 10-g metal rod with 2 mm diameter from 25-mm height.",
